  <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="title:1;4:10">Verifying the Install Using Embedded Tests</title>
  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:1;6:8">Tempest is a set of integration tests for OpenStack API validation, scenarios, and other
      specific tests to be run against a live OpenStack cluster.</p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:2;8:8">A version of the upstream <xref href="http://docs.openstack.org/developer/tempest/" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:1;9:40"><?ditaot usertext?>Tempest</xref> integration tests is pre-deployed in the HP
      Helion OpenStack deployer node.</p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:3;11:8">You can use these embedded tests to verify if the deployed cloud is functional.</p>
    <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="ul:1;12:9">
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:1;13:11">
        <xref href="#tempest/running" type="section" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:2;14:54"><?ditaot usertext?>Running the Tests</xref>
      </li>
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:2;16:11">
        <xref type="section" href="#tempest/results" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:3;17:54"><?ditaot usertext?>Viewing Test Results</xref>
      </li>
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:3;19:11">
        <xref type="section" href="#tempest/custom" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:4;20:53"><?ditaot usertext?>Customizing the Test Run</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:4;23:8">For more information on running Tempest tests, see <xref href="https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/tempest/tree/README.rst" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:5;25:23"><?ditaot usertext?>Tempest - The OpenStack Integration Test Suite</xref>. <note type="important" class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="note:1;26:10">Running these tests requires access to the deployed cloud's identity admin
        credentials</note></p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:5;28:8">Tempest creates and deletes test accounts and test resources for test purposes.</p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:6;29:8">In certain cases Tempest might fail to clean-up some of test resources after a test is
      complete, for example in case of failed tests.</p>
    <section id="running" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="section:1;31:27"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="title:2;31:34">Running the Rests</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:7;32:10">To run the default set of Tempest tests:</p>
      <ol class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="ol:1;33:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:4;34:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:8;35:14">Login to the deployer node.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:5;37:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:9;38:14">Navigate to the ansible folder:</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;39:22">cd ~/scratch/ansible/next/hos/ansible</codeblock>
        </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:6;41:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:10;42:14">Ensure you can access your cloud:</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;43:22">
ansible-playbook -i hosts/verb_hosts cloud-client-setup.yml
source /etc/environment</codeblock>
        </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:7;47:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:11;48:14">Run the tests:</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeblock:3;49:22">ansible-playbook -i hosts/verb_hosts tempest-run.yml</codeblock>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:12;52:10">Optionally, you can <xref type="section" href="#tempest/custom" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:6;52:74"><?ditaot usertext?>customize Tempest to run
          specific tests</xref>.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="results" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="section:2;55:27"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="title:3;55:34">Viewing Test Results</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:13;56:10">Tempest is deployed under <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;56:44">/opt/stack/tempest</codeph>. Test results are written in
        the following log file:</p>
      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeblock:4;58:18">/opt/stack/tempest/testr_results.log </codeblock>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:14;59:10">A detailed log file is written to:
        <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeblock:5;60:20">/opt/stack/tempest/tempest.log</codeblock></p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:15;61:10">The results are also stored in the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;61:53">testrepository</codeph> database.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:16;62:10">To access the results after the run:</p>
      <ol class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="ol:2;63:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:8;64:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:17;65:14">Login to the deployer node.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="li:9;67:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:18;68:14">Change to the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;68:36">tempest</codeph> directory and list the test results:</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="codeblock:6;69:22">
cd /opt/stack/tempest
testr last</codeblock>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:19;74:10">See <xref href="https://testrepository.readthedocs.org/en/latest/" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="xref:7;75:25"><?ditaot usertext?>Test Repository Users Manual</xref> for more details on how to manage the
        test result repository.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="custom" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="section:3;78:26"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="title:4;78:33">Customizing the Test Run</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_verification.dita" xtrc="p:20;79:10">There are several ways available to customize which tests will be executed.</p>
